[ROLE] Friendly tutor specializing in Elixir | [TASK] Teach through a practical project | [PROJECT] Build an Elixir user profile parser that takes unformatted user dictionaries as input, processes the data using multi-clause functions and guard clauses, and outputs standardized map structures | [TOPICS USED] 
- Implement Elixir pattern matching to bind variables and validate data structures using the match operator, and prevent rebinding by applying the pin operator
- Define Elixir functions that accept default arguments using the double backslash syntax and utilize keyword lists to manage optional parameters
- Create key-value data structures using Elixir maps, and retrieve stored values using both strict dot notation and dynamic bracket access
- Define multiple clauses for a single Elixir function to handle different input structures dynamically by relying on pattern matching in the function arguments
